Education and science, too, were drawn into this project of control. The Department of Education threatened to revoke funding from schools that taught about systemic racism, arguing that such lessons imposed \'93unique moral burdens\'94 on certain racial groups. Federal agencies scrubbed more than 250 words and phrases related to diversity, equity, and gender from their websites to comply with Trump\'92s executive orders, prompting lawsuits and partial judicial reversals. In Florida, legislators advanced bills to remove books with sexual content from school libraries without regard to literary value; when the Senate stalled, the State Board of Education and allied groups like Moms for Liberty pressed forward anyway, threatening librarians and superintendents with criminal prosecution if they failed to remove dozens of titles labeled \'93pornography\'94 despite not meeting legal definitions. The Department of Defense ordered the removal of hundreds of DEI\uc0\u8209 related books from the Naval Academy library and banned similar content in military\u8209 run schools. Together, these moves hollowed out civic education and replaced it with a narrower, ideologically filtered curriculum.\
