Economic and environmental policy reflected the same alignment of state power with elite interests. The Environmental Protection Agency drafted plans to eliminate greenhouse\uc0\u8209 gas limits for coal and gas power plants, claiming their emissions were not significant enough to regulate, and moved to weaken the Mercury and Air Toxics Standards. Congress, working with the White House, passed multiple resolutions disapproving EPA rules that had granted California waivers to set stricter vehicle pollution standards and to phase out gas\u8209 powered cars by 2035. Trump signed a resolution blocking California\'92s gas\u8209 car ban and related truck emission rules, prompting lawsuits from California and ten other states. At the same time, the administration proposed deep cuts to the National Park Service\'92s stewardship budget, threatening programs that protect natural soundscapes and night skies. These choices favored fossil\u8209 fuel and industrial interests over public health and climate stability, and they did so through both executive action and legislative performance.\
\
The use of economic levers to punish critics and reward allies extended into civil society. The administration canceled federal grants to the American Bar Association after it criticized Trump, froze billions in grants to Harvard University over its refusal to alter admissions and hiring to include more conservative viewpoints, and sought to revoke the university\'92s tax\uc0\u8209 exempt status. It banned federal funds for grants that used certain gender\u8209 related terms, affecting more than a thousand research projects, and threatened to cut funding to universities that allowed \'93illegal protests,\'94 leading to large losses at institutions like Columbia and policy changes on campus demonstrations. The State Department intervened in the Fulbright Program to require political approval for projects touching on diversity, equity, and inclusion, prompting mass resignations from the Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board. In each case, public money was used not as neutral support for education and research, but as a tool to enforce ideological conformity.\
